channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Where Is the Outrage From the 'Pink Hat' Brigade? Taliban Bans Women's VOICES in Public
Why won't Pennsylvania voters have results on Election Night?
item.description: Pennsylvania Secretary of State Al Schmidt said voters should not expect results on the night of Nov. 5 in a bid to head off repeated 2020 controversy.

item.title: DNC Attendees Test Positive for COVID-19
item.description: A number of attendees at the Democratic National Convention in Chicago last week came away from the event with COVID-19, the New York Post reported Sunday.

item.title: Putin's War, Week 130. White House Says the Quiet Part Out Loud and a Storm Gathers in Southern Ukraine
Minnesotan commutes out of state for 'right to work' after business closed under Walz's COVID-era rules
item.description: Minnesota resident Lisa Zarza commutes two hours a day to work in Wisconsin after losing her businesses under Gov. Tim Walz's COIVD-era policies.

item.title: RFK Jr.: MAGA Recalls 'A Nation Brimming With Vitality'
item.description: Robert F. Kennedy Jr. said Sunday that the term "MAGA," or "Make America Great Again," should be embraced.

item.title: This Is About to Get Ugly
Walz faced another accusation of misrepresentation in unearthed, blistering letter: 'Remove any reference'
item.description: An unearthed 2006 letter from the Nebraska Chamber of Commerce to then-congressional candidate Tim Walz accused him of misrepresenting an award he won.

item.title: Pastor: Evangelicals Can Be Swayed to Vote Harris to Hand Her Election

Who is Kamala Harris' 'combative Marxist economist' father, Donald J. Harris?
item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris' economist father has largely stayed out of the public spotlight, overwhelmingly refraining from discussing his daughter publicly.

item.title: Butker: J.D. Vance Should 'Defend the Unborn'
item.description: Kansas City Chiefs kicker Harrison Butker called on former President Donald Trump's running mate, Sen. J.D. Vance of Ohio, to "defend the unborn" after Trump on Friday posted to Truth Social that his "Administration will be great for women and their reproductive rights."

item.title: Elon and Tucker Speak Up for Pavel Durov and the Present Danger to Free Speech
Harris' push for electric vehicles suffers another blow after automaker backtracks: 'Unwanted and unworkable'
item.description: Ford is backing away from rolling out electric vehicles in favor of hybrid options, indicating more defeats to Harris-backed electric vehicle initiatives.

item.title: Rep. Donalds: Harris Can't Distance Herself From Biden
item.description: Rep. Byron Donalds, R-Fla, believes Vice President Kamala Harris may be unable to win the 2024 election since she cannot feasibly distance herself from President Joe Biden.
